name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.datanode.transfer.socket.send.buffer.size
description:
Socket send buffer size for DataXceiver (mirroring packets to downstream
    in pipeline). This may affect TCP connection throughput.
    If it is set to zero or negative value, no buffer size will be set
    explicitly, thus enable tcp auto-tuning on some system.
    The default value is 0.

name: dfs.datanode.slow.io.warning.threshold.ms
description:
The threshold in milliseconds at which we will log a slow
    io warning in a datanode. By default, this parameter is set to 300
    milliseconds.

name: dfs.namenode.redundancy.interval.seconds
description:
The periodicity in seconds with which the namenode computes 
  low redundancy work for datanodes. Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive),
  as described in dfs.heartbeat.interval.

name: fs.s3a.threads.keepalivetime
description:
Number of seconds a thread can be idle before being
    terminated.

name: ha.health-monitor.rpc.connect.max.retries
description:
The number of retries on connect error when establishing RPC proxy
    connection to NameNode, used for monitorHealth() calls.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.move.thread-count
description: The number of threads used to move files.

name: dfs.datanode.data.dir.perm
description:
Permissions for the directories on on the local filesystem where
  the DFS data node store its blocks. The permissions can either be octal or
  symbolic.

name: mapreduce.shuffle.pathcache.max-weight
description: The maximum total weight of entries the cache may contain.
